While trying to import space/s through script, if accidentally existing space is re-imported without knowledge, if we do not have access to the UI there is nowhere to tell why the import failed.

Below is the last line/hint being printed in the atlassian-confluence.log
{code:java}
2021-11-23 11:07:57,503 INFO [http-nio-8090-exec-9] [atlassian.confluence.upgrade.AbstractUpgradeManager] getOldestSpaceImportAllowed Compatibility of Space Import: 4517 Upgrade task "Migrate all Page Templates using a storage format round-trip conversion" prevents importing
{code}
At the same time in the UI I see an error which reads "A space with the key 'xyz' already exists. Please delete it before restoring a space with the same key." But for scenarios, where UI access is not available for some reasons, it becomes difficult, tried adding com.atlassian.hibernate.extras.XMLDatabinder & com.atlassian.confluence.importexport in DEBUG/TRACE but no signs of the error we saw in the UI.

Even went onto to check at the code level for the class that is responsible for printing this error in the UI, placed the below class in DEBUG/TRACE but nothing additional was printed on the application logs linking to the failure:
{code:java}
import com.atlassian.confluence.content.render.xhtml.migration.SiteMigrator
{code}

In Exchange online, the main method of authentication to mail servers is now Oauth 2.0. ([Authenticate an IMAP, POP or SMTP connection using OAuth \- Microsoft Docs|https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/exchange/client-developer/legacy-protocols/how-to-authenticate-an-imap-pop-smtp-application-by-using-oauth])

They have began to phase out all Basic authentication (see [End of support for Basic Authentication access to Exchange Online API's for Office 365 customers \- Microsoft 365 Developer Blog|https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/office/blogs/end-of-support-for-basic-authentication-access-to-exchange-online-apis-for-office-365-customers/]) except for SMTP for the time being:

{quote}
Please note this change does not affect SMTP AUTH and we will continue to support Basic Authentication for it in Exchange Online at this time. With the large number of solutions, devices, and appliances that use SMTP for sending mail we are working on ways to further secure SMTP AUTH and will continue to update you as we make progress. 
{quote}

Suggesting that we should look into adding mail server Oauth 2.0 support for authentication.

h3. Issue Summary

If user add a tab or space in the first line of a code in code block macro to indent the code as per their need, whitespace is not honored.
{quote}According to the [Code Block Macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/code-block-macro-139390.html] documentation, any white space contained in the placeholder is not manipulated in any way by the Code Block macro. This is to provide the writer with flexibility over code indentation.
{quote}
However, in this case, the space or tab in the first line is not retained in the code block macro.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add some sample text or code in the code block macro for eg:
 ** 
{code:java}
if (issue.getTimeSpent()) {
   def TimeSpent issue.getTimeSpent() 17.75 /60 /60 as Double
   return Time Spent.round(2) }
{code}
 # Add tab in the first line of the code so code looks as below: 
 ** 
{code:java}
   if (issue.getTimeSpent()) {
   def TimeSpent issue.getTimeSpent() 17.75 /60 /60 as Double
   return Time Spent.round(2) }
{code}
 # Save the code block macro and indentation beaks. 
 # Refer to the attached recording for more information

h3. Expected Results

The code block macro should retain the tab in the first line of the code
h3. Actual Results

The tab is removed from the first line losing the indentation of the code.
h3. Workaround

If we add the below HTML entity of non-breaking space in the first line before adding the tab, the tab or the space is honored.
{code}
&nbsp;
{code}
